OL,3,CThames Water defends #1.4bn Abingdon
OL,4,Creservoir proposal
OL,6,FLeonie Dubois, Thames Water's Head of
OL,7,FEngagement, Land and Consents said:
OL,8,F"We recognise if you live close to
OL,9,Finfrastructure you may have concerns
OL,10,Fabout what that means to you.
OL,12,F"It's why we are urging people to talk
OL,13,Fto us to see the possibility and the
OL,14,Fopportunity to have this near to them."
OL,16,FDubois said that they want to know if
OL,17,Flocals want things like sailing on the
OL,18,Freservoir, dog walking routes or even
OL,19,Fcafes.
