OL,3,CThames Water defends #1.4bn Abingdon
OL,4,Creservoir proposal
OL,6,F"The opportunity for two-way
OL,7,Fconversation is an important part of
OL,8,Fthe consultation process, and we
OL,9,Fgenuinely want to hear people's views
OL,10,Fand hopefully help to alleviate their
OL,11,Fconcerns."
OL,13,FIt comes as campaigners against say it
OL,14,Fwill completely destroy local
OL,15,Fhabitats. Just under 2000 people have
OL,16,Falready signed a petition against the
OL,17,Freservoir with critics saying the
OL,18,Fmoney should be spent on fixing leaks
OL,19,Fand updating existing infrastructure
OL,20,Finstead.
